article.headline: Pennsylvania 84, Cornell 44
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber had 20 points, eight assists and seven steals to lead Penn to an 84-44 victory over Cornell on Friday night in the Ivy League opener for both teams. Eric Osmundson scored 15 points and Mark Zoller had 12 for Penn (7-5, 1-0 Ivy League), the defending league champions. Jason Hartford had 10 points for the Big Red (5-10, 0-1), who committed 25 turnovers in the game. The Quakers went on a 19-0 run at the start of the second half while holding Cornell scoreless for 5:55. The Big Red's Adam Gore finally scored a 3-pointer, but Penn then went on a 21-5 run to build a 74-33 lead with 7:21 left to play. Penn never trailed and jumped out to a 27-13 lead with 5:20 left in the first half, holding a 34-25 advantage at the break. Jaaber had 10 points in the half and helped force 17 Big Red turnovers. Cornell, coached by longtime Penn assistant Steve Donahue, has now lost 15 straight to the Quakers.
